          <!-- FAQ content-->
          <div class="modal-content">
            <!-- First content -->
            <div class="modal-header">
              <h4 class="modal-title" align="middle">Why Doesn't The Join Button Do Anything??</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
              <p>The join button is not linked to completely and does not have full functionality. It simply shows you that the event has been joined, and it gives you an option to cancel it. This is all feax functionality.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Second content -->
            <div class="modal-header">
              <h4 class="modal-title" align="middle">How Come The Logout Button Doesn't Do Anything??</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
              <p>Since we were not able to stick with Firebase, that did not let us keep the convenient Google sign in. So, the logout feature simply says that you are logged out, but you are not, because you never signed in officialy in the first place.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Third content -->
            <div class="modal-header">
              <h4 class="modal-title" align="middle">What Can I Do On This Site?</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
              <p>Once you have been logged in, you will be given options in the sidebar menu which allow you to create and browse events. You may also check the events that you have created and joined. All conveniently placed on one page.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <!-- _________________________ PAGE CONTENT ENDS HERE _________________________ -->

